        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 6:14PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 613 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Taylorsville, or 7 miles east of Cedar Rock, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Taylorsville, Bethlehem, Lake Hickory, Ellendale, Little River In
Alexander County, and Kings Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
